task.summary: Created Simulation Functions file and ran simulation to determine market history. I have unduely high variation (i.e. it appears as though the market behavior is incredibly erratic, even for different alpha ranges. (the resultant graphs are in clear disagreement with the top of pg 6 of Morro's Summary work.

I've established a test build to find out what leads to the indeterminancy in my procedurally generated strategies. We want a new-ish strategy for every call with a unique parameter, but the same strategy for every given parameter. I'm playing with the staticness of elements of the functions, but I'll likely need to establish some catch protocols to test what exactly is happening.

I've written a check for all parts of the project, and that they all work together, and detailed how the code works line by line in plain English in a doc titled "Code Walk Through". After all checks, I realize that the static-calls of the functions do nothing, and of the generators lead to non-deterministic outputs. (i.e. static calling the ms19937 generator with the same value leads to different results when we then generate from it) This gives random values, unlike what we want. However, with the present implementation, there appears to be far greater consensus than the literature suggests. The periodicity/quasi-randomness is seen at approximately appropriate values of alpha, but the variation in attendance is consistently higher than referenced in literature. (i.e. nearly over the whole range) However, after checking everything, I have run out of ideas as to what's causing the difference.

The code has been rewritten in terms of strategy, agent and experiment structs and there is complete catch_debug code in place. Unfortunately, it will not preform a single iteration of "run" minority game, however...
Tested Random generator for bias in generator seed effect, attempted Diehard tests. Synicing.
Created distribution of memory agent initialization functions, though the Normal dist (bell curve) and exponential could use more work.
Syncing, created a loop to average through different seeding w.r.t. agent strategies.
Brought previous master graph function in place, still need to break down header files
Final functional version, though variance does seem to spread a bit, at critical alpha, and further the code still needs to be properly assembled from the header files.
Added memory initialization functions for Alpha agents, and generalized functions for use in other agents
Fixed general memory initializations, last push before TMG and evolutionary edits
fixed evolutionary component, made Thermal Minority Game functions applicable for all agent types
added evolutionary functions, master functions for multiple printing
